<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,991,1552]" pageId="0" pageNumber="298">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savchenko &amp; Lareschi" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,365,1060,1084]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Laelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="0" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schatzi">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="298">Laelaps schatzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of the female. The species is unique in having short genitoventral setae (≤114 μm), reticulated surface pattern on the genital shield from the level of 
<emphasis box="[1003,1043,1096,1120]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="298">Zv1</emphasis>
to the posterior margin, and by the presence of one or two additional unpaired setae between 
<emphasis box="[774,799,1132,1156]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="298">J4</emphasis>
on the dorsal shield. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Savchenko, E. &amp; Lareschi, M." box="[1076,1397,1132,1156]" pageId="0" pageNumber="298" pagination="105146" refId="ref2079" refString="Savchenko, E. &amp; Lareschi, M. (2019) A new species of Laelaps Koch, 1836 (Mesostigmata: Laelapidae) parasitic of the sigmodontine rodent Oligoryzomys flavescens Waterhouse, 1837 (Rodentia: Cricetidae): Molecular and morphological characterization. Acta Tropica, 199, 105146. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. actatropica. 2019.105146" type="journal article" year="2019">Savchenko &amp; Lareschi (2019)</bibRefCitation>
for the full description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
